#### 2. Add a Custom Liquid Block

- In the theme editor sidebar, navigate to the **Footer** section.
- Click **Add block** and select **Custom Liquid**.
- Position this block at the end of the footer to ensure it loads after the rest of the content.

#### 3. Insert the JavaScript Code

In the **Custom Liquid** block, you'll add a `<script>` tag containing the JavaScript code. Here's how you can do it:

```liquid
<script>
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
    // Function to check if the form-embed element exists
    function applyCustomStyles() {
      const formEmbed = document.getElementById('app-embed-container-2072');
      if (formEmbed && formEmbed.shadowRoot) {
        const shadowRoot = formEmbed.shadowRoot;

        // Inject custom styles into the shadow root
